threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects creation of a new service via "sc" command or the powershell "new-service" cmdlet with suspicious binary paths

match_context.values: @{CommandLine=C:\Windows\System32\sc.exe create qhsvagwd binPath= C:\Windows\SysWOW64\qhsvagwd\szgjymfp.exe /d\C:\Users\<USER>\Downloads\xedqyygk.exe\ type= own start= auto DisplayName= wifi support; Image=C:\Windows\System32\sc.exe; EventID=1}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Read Contents From Stdin Via Cmd.EXE
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detect the use of "<" to read and potentially execute a file via cmd.exe

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: New Firewall Rule Added Via Netsh.EXE
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the addition of a new rule to the Windows firewall via netsh

match_context.values: @{CommandLine="C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe" advfirewall firewall add rule name="Host-process for services of Windows" dir=in action=allow program="C:\Windows\SysWOW64\svchost.exe" enable=yes>nul; Image=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe; EventID=1}

@{CommandLine=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe advfirewall firewall add rule name=Host-process for services of Windows dir=in action=allow program=C:\Windows\SysWOW64\svchost.exe enable=yes>nul; Image=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe; EventID=1}

@{CommandLine="%windir%\System32\netsh.exe" advfirewall firewall add rule name="Host-process for services of Windows" dir=in action=allow program="%windir%\SysWOW64\svchost.exe" enable=yes>nul; Image=%windir%\System32\netsh.exe; EventID=1}
